  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 8 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 1 critical, 11 high, 9 medium, 18 normal. Key bases needing attention include Chişinău (RMO/LUKK), Bucharest Henri Coandă (OTP/LROP) and Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD); plus 9 other bases. 9 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is mist, fog / freezing fog and very low visibility  — most notably around Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ), Craiova (CRA/LRCV) and Suceava Stefan cel Mare (SCV/LRSV). Network hotspots: Malmö Sturup (MMX/ESMS), Trieste–Friuli Venezia Giulia (TRS/LIPQ), Turku (TKU/EFTU), Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM), Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO) and 3 others. Primary drivers: very low visibility, low cloud base and fog / freezing fog. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 9 airports changed status, led by Turku (TKU/EFTU), Billund (BLL/EKBI), Almaty (ALA/UAAA) and 6 others.",
